'''Google Inc.''' ({{nasdaq|GOOG}} and {{lse|GGEA}}) is an [[United States|American]] [[public company|public corporation]], specializing in [[Internet search]] and [[online advertising]]. Google was co-founded by [[Larry Page]] and [[Sergey Brin]] while they were students at [[Stanford University]], and the company was first incorporated as a [[privately held company]] on [[September 7]] [[1998]]. Google's [[initial public offering]] took place on [[August 19]], [[2004]], raising [[United States Dollar|$]]1.67 billion, making it worth $23 billion.<ref name="washpost">Webb, Cynthia L. "[http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A14939-2004Aug19.html Google's IPO: Grate Expectations]." ''[[Washington Post]].'' [[August 19]], [[2004]]. Retrieved on [[February 25]], [[2007]].</ref> The company grew rapidly since its IPO, acquiring smaller companies such as Writely, [[JotSpot]], and online video sharing site [[YouTube]] in [[2006]], and moving into the office software market with the release of its [[Google Apps|Google Apps Premium Edition]] in [[2007]]. Additionally, Google is also involved in many cooperational partnerships with other corporations, such as [[NASA]], [[Sun Microsystems]], [[Time Warner]]'s [[America Online]], and [[NewsCorp]]'s [[MySpace]].
